In this JSON object, we have a list of test cases. Each test case has the following properties:

- `id`: Unique identifier for the test case
- `type`: Type of testing (functional)
- `title`: Title of the user story or feature being tested
- `priority`: Priority level of the test case
- `steps`: List of individual steps required to execute the test case
- `result`: Expected result of the test case (Pass/Fail)
- `reason`: Reason for passing or failing the test case (empty for now, but can be populated later)
- `notes`: Additional notes about the test case

The `steps` property is a list of individual steps that need to be executed to test the user story. Each step has its own properties:

- `step_id`: Unique identifier for the step
- `description`: Brief description of the step
- `preconditions`: List of preconditions required to execute the step (e.g., login form is visible)
- `input_values`: List of input values needed to execute the step (e.g., username and password)
- `expected_result`: Expected result of the step

This format can be easily extended or modified as needed.